4. TELEMETRY AND PRIVACY

   The Software includes an anonymous telemetry system designed to
   comply with LGPD (Brazil), GDPR (EU), and equivalent privacy
   regulations worldwide. The telemetry:

   (a) Does NOT collect personal data;
   (b) Does NOT collect or store raw IP addresses (IPs are hashed
       with a one-way function before any storage);
   (c) Does NOT collect hostnames, user-agents, or browser fingerprints;
   (d) Uses a randomly generated UUID as instance identifier, not
       tied to any person;
   (e) Transmits only aggregated usage counters (sessions, connections,
       active rooms) and technical metadata (OS platform, architecture,
       Node.js version);
   (f) Can be audited in the source code at server/src/telemetry.ts.

